# Forge in Cursor

Universal Forge behavior (**blocking prompts**, **stage-local questioning**, **interactive human input**) is defined once in **`skills/using-forge/SKILL.md`** for **every** supported IDE — not Cursor-only. This file adds **Cursor-specific** tool aliases and reminders.

Forge skills load from **`~/.cursor/plugins/local/forge/skills/`** after **`scripts/install.sh --platform cursor`**. On every session start, read **`~/.cursor/plugins/local/forge/skills/using-forge/SKILL.md`**. Key commands include **`/forge`**, **`/workspace`**, **`/intake`**, **`/qa`**, **`/qa-write`**, **`/qa-run`** — full list in plugin **`commands/`**.

## `AskUserQuestion` → `AskQuestion` (Cursor alias)

Forge **`SKILL.md`** files name the blocking multiple-choice tool **`AskUserQuestion`** (canonical for Claude Code, `allowed-tools` policy, CI). **In Cursor sessions, use `AskQuestion`** with the same title, text, and options — same semantics as **`using-forge`** **Blocking interactive prompts**.

If `AskQuestion` is not available or a call fails, present the same choices as a **numbered list** in the assistant message, **stop**, and wait for the user. Do not skip skill gates that depend on a human answer.

**Do not** mass-rename `AskUserQuestion` in `SKILL.md` files; keep skills canonical for other hosts and CI.

## Interactive human input (project standard — all hosts)

Any **doubt, question, confirmation, or choice** that needs a human answer — including **task-id**, **next step**, **waiver**, **priority** — must use a **blocking interactive prompt** or **numbered list + stop**, not prose-only *“reply if…”* walls. In Cursor that is usually **`AskQuestion`**. Full norm: **`using-forge`** → **Interactive human input** (applies to Gemini CLI, JetBrains, Codex, etc., with host mapping in that skill).

## Chat-visible interrogation (QA, intake, any “questions in thread” HARD-GATE)

Some Forge skills require the **full question text** to appear in the **assistant message** (markdown), **not** only inside the blocking prompt UI, **not** only in a file write, **not** only in a modal body the user never scrolls past. Examples: **`qa-prd-analysis`** Step 0.5 (**paste complete Q1–Q7 blocks first**), **`intake-interrogate`** Q9 verbatim blockquote.

**In Cursor you MUST:** (1) Output those blocks in plain assistant markdown in the **same turn** before **`AskQuestion`**. (2) Then call **`AskQuestion`** if appropriate. Skipping (1) invalidates the gate — the transcript shows nothing the user was asked.

**Why this breaks more often in Cursor than in some other hosts:** `hooks/hooks-cursor.json` documents that Cursor has **no** `UserPromptSubmit`-style hook; Forge cannot reinject “next gate / ask Q1–Q7” on **every** user message. Only **session-start** runs. So nothing apart from **this rule + the skill text** forces the model to show questions — **you** must follow the skill literally.

**If the user says questions never appeared:** Re-run the phase and paste this into the prompt: *“Follow `skills/qa-prd-analysis/SKILL.md` Step 0.5 HARD-GATE — print Q1–Q7 in full in chat, then wait for answers; do not write only to brain.”*

## Automation ≠ assumption

Forge **automates artifacts and pipelines** — not **decisions**. At every **needle-moving** step (scope, design authority, QA interrogation, CSV/eval ordering waivers, prioritization), use **`AskQuestion`** (or numbered choices) and **wait**. Do **not** infer “confirmed” answers or waiver frontmatter from docs alone; see **`using-forge`**.

**Stage-local questioning — respect process order:** Ask only what unblocks the **current** Forge stage (or the **next** prerequisite in dependency order). **Do not** open with a **blocking prompt** about **later** phases — merge, eval harness, council contracts, tech-plan approval, QA CSV, design ingest, PR strategy — when the pipeline **has not reached** that stage or **upstream** prerequisites are still missing. Fix the **first** gap first. Full norm in **`using-forge`** → **Stage-local questioning**.

**QA→eval slice (when applicable):** If **`prd-locked`** or **`qa-analysis`** is missing, **do not** ask about **eval YAML or CSV waiver** first — intake → **`qa-prd-analysis`** → manual CSV (or waiver) → then YAML. See **`qa-write-scenarios`** **Step −1**.
